What do you think about keeping this interface the same and instead changing the private members left and right to DruidRel<?>
Whenever left and right is set - we can do something like this.left = getCheapestDruidRel(RelNode);
As it's written, I wonder if it's possible for us to estimate that a subquery is not required in the computeSelfCost function, but the DruidRel used to build the native query actually uses a subquery.

